 x-terminal emulator must provide option -T.
 See 11.8.3 Packages providing a terminal emulator
 http://www.debian.org/doc/debian-policy/ch-customized-programs.html#s11.8.3

---
 st.1 |   16 ++++++++--------
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

--- a/st.1
+++ b/st.1
@@ -12,7 +12,7 @@
 .IR geometry ]
 .RB [ \-o
 .IR file ]
-.RB [ \-t 
+.RB [ \-T
 .IR title ]
 .RB [ \-w 
 .IR windowid ]
@@ -38,10 +38,10 @@
 .BI \-f " font"
 defines the
 .I font
-to use when st is run.
+to use.
 .TP
 .BI \-g " geometry"
-defines the X11 geometry string, which will fixate the height and width of st. 
+defines the X11 geometry string, which will fixate the height and width.
 The form is [=][<width>{xX}<height>][{+-}<xoffset>{+-}<yoffset>]. See
 .BR XParseGeometry (3)
 for further details.
@@ -49,21 +49,21 @@
